<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<!--
  v1.30.2 launchd-hang fix. The companion-CLI helper is a Developer ID
  LaunchAgent that rendezvouses with the sandboxed MAS app via the app-group
  container (~/Library/Group Containers/group.yyh.CLI-Pulse/): the UDS socket
  + auth token live there because it is the ONLY path a sandboxed app and an
  external helper can both reach.

  On macOS 26, a launchd agent WITHOUT this entitlement that touches another
  app's group container blocks IN-KERNEL (os.open never returns; the process
  becomes unkillable until reboot) — observed when a .pkg upgrade replaced the
  helper binary, invalidating the per-cdhash Full Disk Access grant the old
  binary had relied on. Signing the helper with the matching application-group
  grants the access directly, so the daemon binds the socket under launchd
  without needing FDA. See PROJECT_FIX_2026-06-18_helper-launchd-entitlement.md.
-->
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
    <key>com.apple.security.application-groups</key>
    <array>
        <string>group.yyh.CLI-Pulse</string>
    </array>
</dict>
</plist>
